# Onboarding Guide

## Overview
Guidance for new team members and AI assistants to work with n8n-workflow-all-templates effectively.

## Project Setup

### 1. Prerequisites
- Node.js (v16 or higher)
- Python 3.x (for scraper)
- Git
- IDE (VS Code recommended)

### 2. Initial Setup
```bash
# Clone repository
git clone [repository-url]
cd n8n-workflow-all-templates

# Install explorer dependencies
cd explorer && npm install && cd ..

# Build static index for Browse (required)
npm run build:index
npm run copy:index
```

### 3. Environment Variables

**Explorer** (for Templates page with Supabase):
```bash
cp explorer/.env.local.example explorer/.env.local
# Set NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
```

**Scraper** (for syncing to Supabase):
```bash
cp scripts/scraper/.env.example scripts/scraper/.env
# Set SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
```

### 4. Run Development
```bash
npm run dev   # Runs Next.js explorer from root
```

### 5. Scraper (optional)
```bash
npm run scrape        # Sync from api.n8n.io
npm run scrape:local  # Load from local n8n-workflow-all-templates/*.json
```

## Project Structure

```
n8n-workflow-all-templates/
├── explorer/                    # Next.js app
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── app/                 # Browse, Templates routes
│   │   ├── components/          # TemplateCard, WorkflowViewer, etc.
│   │   ├── hooks/               # useIndexTemplates, useTemplateSearch
│   │   ├── lib/                 # supabase, n8n-to-reactflow
│   │   └── types/
│   └── public/
│       └── templates-index.json # Must exist for Browse
├── scripts/scraper/             # Python scraper
├── n8n-workflow-all-templates/  # 7400+ workflow JSON files
└── webapp/                      # Legacy Vite app
```

